rlDnsCl.name: rlDnsCl
rlDnsCl.contactinfo: Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose , CA 95134-1706 USA Website: Cisco Small Business Home http://www.cisco.com/smb>;, Cisco Small Business Support Community <http://www.cisco.com/go/smallbizsupport>
rlDnsCl.description: The MIB module describes the private MIB for DNS supported by CISCOSB's software and products.

rlDnsClv2DomainNameTable.name: rlDnsClv2DomainNameTable
rlDnsClv2DomainNameTable.description: The domain names table for DNS client ver2.

rlDnsClv2DomainNameEntry.name: rlDnsClv2DomainNameEntry
rlDnsClv2DomainNameEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlDnsClv2DomainNameSource.name: rlDnsClv2DomainNameSource
rlDnsClv2DomainNameSource.description: The domain name source. 'static' if defined by user through CLI, 'dhcpv6' or 'dhcpv4' if received by DHCP network protocol.

rlDnsClv2DomainNameIfIndex.name: rlDnsClv2DomainNameIfIndex
rlDnsClv2DomainNameIfIndex.description: The IfIndex from which the domain-name configuration was received, for static entries, value will always be 1.

rlDnsClv2DomainNamePreference.name: rlDnsClv2DomainNamePreference
rlDnsClv2DomainNamePreference.description: This value identifies the preference of domain-name, The lower the value, the more desirable the resolver considers this domain-name in domain-search-list.

rlDnsClv2DomainNameRowStatus.name: rlDnsClv2DomainNameRowStatus
rlDnsClv2DomainNameRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

rlDnsClv2ServersTable.name: rlDnsClv2ServersTable
rlDnsClv2ServersTable.description: The DNS servers table for DNS client ver2.

rlDnsClv2ServersEntry.name: rlDnsClv2ServersEntry
rlDnsClv2ServersEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlDnsClv2ServersSource.name: rlDnsClv2ServersSource
rlDnsClv2ServersSource.description: The DNS servers source. Static if defined by user through CLI, dhcpv6 or dhcpv4 if received by network protocol DHCPv6 or DHCPv4.

rlDnsClv2ServersIfIndex.name: rlDnsClv2ServersIfIndex
rlDnsClv2ServersIfIndex.description: The IfIndex from which the DNS-server configuration was received, for static entries, value will always be 1.

rlDnsClv2ServersPreference.name: rlDnsClv2ServersPreference
rlDnsClv2ServersPreference.description: This value identifies the preference for the name server identified in this row of the table. The lower the value, the more desirable the resolver considers this server.

rlDnsClv2ServersAddrType.name: rlDnsClv2ServersAddrType
rlDnsClv2ServersAddrType.description: The address type of rlDnsClv2ServersInetAddr. Only IPv4, IPv4z, IPv6, and IPv6z addresses are expected, or unknown(0) if datagrams for all local IP addresses are accepted.

rlDnsClv2ServersInetAddr.name: rlDnsClv2ServersInetAddr
rlDnsClv2ServersInetAddr.description: The IP address of the name server identified by this row of the table.

rlDnsClv2ServersSubTree.name: rlDnsClv2ServersSubTree
rlDnsClv2ServersSubTree.description: Queries sent to the name server identified by this row of the table are limited to those for names in the name subtree identified by this variable. If no such limitation applies, the value of this variable is the name of the root domain (a DNS name consisting of a single zero octet).

rlDnsClv2ServersClass.name: rlDnsClv2ServersClass
rlDnsClv2ServersClass.description: The class of DNS queries that will be sent to the server identified by this row of the table.

rlDnsClv2ServersRowStatus.name: rlDnsClv2ServersRowStatus
rlDnsClv2ServersRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

rlDnsClv2FixedTable.name: rlDnsClv2FixedTable
rlDnsClv2FixedTable.description: Read-Only MIB for 'fixed' DNS names. when a DNS entry is fixed, a refresh operation is invoked periodically, to make sure the entry is kept 'warm' in the DNS cache. if the refresh operation fails, the DNSCL will enter a polling state, and will retry to resolve the entry again in constant intervals. polling-interval duration for unresolved entries is configurable by MIB scalar 'rlDnsClMinPollingInterval'.

rlDnsClv2FixedEntry.name: rlDnsClv2FixedEntry
rlDnsClv2FixedEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlDnsClv2FixedName.name: rlDnsClv2FixedName
rlDnsClv2FixedName.description: DNS name of FIXED domain name

rlDnsClv2FixedType.name: rlDnsClv2FixedType
rlDnsClv2FixedType.description: requested type of Resource Record for the current resolved fixed entry. for e.g - A (IPv4), AAAA (IPv6)

rlDnsClv2FixedPrettyName.name: rlDnsClv2FixedPrettyName
rlDnsClv2FixedPrettyName.description: Name of the RR at this row in the table. This is identical to the rlDnsClv2FixedName variable, except that character case is preserved in this variable, per DNS conventions.

rlDnsClv2FixedState.name: rlDnsClv2FixedState
rlDnsClv2FixedState.description: current state of fixed entry. unresolved entries are in 'polling' state.

rlDnsClv2FixedCounter.name: rlDnsClv2FixedCounter
rlDnsClv2FixedCounter.description: Number of 'fix' requests for this DNS name & type

rlDnsClv2FixedTTL.name: rlDnsClv2FixedTTL
rlDnsClv2FixedTTL.description: Remaining TTL of resolved fixed entry

rlDnsClv2FixedTTRefresh.name: rlDnsClv2FixedTTRefresh
rlDnsClv2FixedTTRefresh.description: Remaining time-to-refresh of resolved fixed entry

rlDnsClv2FixedTTPolling.name: rlDnsClv2FixedTTPolling
rlDnsClv2FixedTTPolling.description: Remaining polling-interval time of unresolved fixed entry

rlDnsClv2ClearCacheTable.name: rlDnsClv2ClearCacheTable
rlDnsClv2ClearCacheTable.description: action MIB for clearing DNS cache tables, 'static' option will clear all statically configured hostname-to-IP mappings, 'dynamic' option will clear both negative & positive cache from dynamic (DNS) entries, 'all' will clear all entries (static & dynamic) in static, positive & negative cache.

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheTable.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheTable
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheTable.description: Unified DNS Cache Table (static,dynamic & fixed entries). This is a read-only MIB for presentation purposes.

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheEntry.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheEntry
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheState.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheState
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheState.description: The state of the current cache entry

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheType.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheType
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheType.description: IP address type of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table. for negative/unresolved entries the 'noResolution' value is returned.

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheIndex.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheIndex
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheIndex.description: A value which makes entries in the table unique when the other index values do not provide a unique index.

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheInetAddrType.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheInetAddrType
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheInetAddrType.description: The INET address type of rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheInetAddr, for e.g IPv4, IPv6, IPv6z or UNKNOWN

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheInetAddr.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheInetAddr
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheInetAddr.description: Resolved IP Address of given Domain-Name

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheTTL.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheTTL
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheTTL.description: Time-To-Live of RR in DNS cache. This is the initial TTL value which was received with the RR when it was originally received. for unresolved entries, will return the polling interval instead of TTL

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheRemainingTTL.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheRemainingTTL
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheRemainingTTL.description: Remaining TTL seconds since RR was received. For unresolved entries, will return remaining time till next retry

rlDnsClv2UnifiedCachePrettyName.name: rlDnsClv2UnifiedCachePrettyName
rlDnsClv2UnifiedCachePrettyName.description: Name of the RR at this row in the table. This is identical to the rlDnsClv2UnifiedCacheName variable, except that character case is preserved in this variable, per DNS conventions.

rlDnsClMibVersion.name: rlDnsClMibVersion
rlDnsClMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 1.

rlDnsClEnable.name: rlDnsClEnable
rlDnsClEnable.description: Enable or Disable the use of the DNS client feature.

rlDnsClDomainNameEntry.name: rlDnsClDomainNameEntry
rlDnsClDomainNameEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlDnsClDomainNameName.name: rlDnsClDomainNameName
rlDnsClDomainNameName.description: The domain name for this ifIndex.

rlDnsClDomainNameOwner.name: rlDnsClDomainNameOwner
rlDnsClDomainNameOwner.description: The Domain Name owner. Static if Domain Name defined by user, dhcp if received by boot protocol like DHCP.

rlDnsClDomainNameRowStatus.name: rlDnsClDomainNameRowStatus
rlDnsClDomainNameRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

rlDnsClMaxNumOfRetransmissions.name: rlDnsClMaxNumOfRetransmissions
rlDnsClMaxNumOfRetransmissions.description: The maximum number of retransmissions for each query.

rlDnsClMinRetransmissionInterval.name: rlDnsClMinRetransmissionInterval
rlDnsClMinRetransmissionInterval.description: The minimum number of seconds that must elapsed before retransmission for each query.

rlDnsClNamesEntry.name: rlDnsClNamesEntry
rlDnsClNamesEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlDnsClNamesOwner.name: rlDnsClNamesOwner
rlDnsClNamesOwner.description: The Host Name Entry owner. Static if Host Name Entry defined by user, dhcp if received by boot protocol like DHCP.

rlDnsClNamesIndex.name: rlDnsClNamesIndex
rlDnsClNamesIndex.description: A value which makes entries in the table unique when the other index values (rlDnsClNamesName) do not provide a unique index.

rlDnsClNamesRowStatus.name: rlDnsClNamesRowStatus
rlDnsClNamesRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtTable.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtTable
rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtTable.description: Augmenting rlDnsResConfigSbeltTable (dns resolver safety belt table) for added info

rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtEntry.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtEntry
rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtEntry.description: A row of the table rlDnsResConfigSbeltTable Extended by this definition.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltOwner.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltOwner
rlDnsResConfigSbeltOwner.description: The DNS server Entry owner. Static if DNS server Entry defined by user, dhcp if received by boot protocol like DHCP.

rlDnsClNamesInetEntry.name: rlDnsClNamesInetEntry
rlDnsClNamesInetEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlDnsClNamesInetOwner.name: rlDnsClNamesInetOwner
rlDnsClNamesInetOwner.description: The Host Name Entry owner. Static if Host Name Entry defined by user, dhcp if received by boot protocol like DHCP.

rlDnsClNamesInetIndex.name: rlDnsClNamesInetIndex
rlDnsClNamesInetIndex.description: A value which makes entries in the table unique when the other index values (rlDnsClNamesName) do not provide a unique index.

rlDnsClNamesInetRRType.name: rlDnsClNamesInetRRType
rlDnsClNamesInetRRType.description: DNS type of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table. The user can configure 'a' or 'aaaa' types only.

rlDnsClNamesInetAddrType.name: rlDnsClNamesInetAddrType
rlDnsClNamesInetAddrType.description: The address type of rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSource. Only IPv4, IPv4z, IPv6, and IPv6z addresses are expected, or unknown(0) if datagrams for all local IP addresses are accepted.

rlDnsClNamesInetRowStatus.name: rlDnsClNamesInetRowStatus
rlDnsClNamesInetRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetTable.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetTable
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetTable.description: Table of safety belt information used by the resolver when it hasn't got any better idea of where to send a query, such as when the resolver is booting or is a stub resolver.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetEntry.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetEntry
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetEntry.description: An entry in the resolver's Sbelt table. Rows may be created or deleted at any time by the DNS resolver and by SNMP SET requests. Whether the values changed via SNMP are saved in stable storage across `reset' operations is implementation-specific.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetAddrType.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetAddrType
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetAddrType.description: The address type of rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetAddr. Only IPv4, IPv4z, IPv6, and IPv6z addresses are expected, or unknown(0) if datagrams for all local IP addresses are accepted.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetAddr.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetAddr
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetAddr.description: The IP address of the Sbelt name server identified by this row of the table.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetName.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetName
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetName.description: The DNS name of a Sbelt nameserver identified by this row of the table. A zero-length string indicates that the name is not known by the resolver.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetRecursion.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetRecursion
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetRecursion.description: Kind of queries resolver will be sending to the name server identified in this row of the table: iterative(1) indicates that resolver will be directing iterative queries to this name server (RD bit turned off). recursive(2) indicates that resolver will be directing recursive queries to this name server (RD bit turned on). recursiveAndIterative(3) indicates that the resolver will be directing both recursive and iterative queries to the server identified in this row of the table.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetPref.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetPref
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetPref.description: This value identifies the preference for the name server identified in this row of the table. The lower the value, the more desirable the resolver considers this server.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetSubTree.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetSubTree
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetSubTree.description: Queries sent to the name server identified by this row of the table are limited to those for names in the name subtree identified by this variable. If no such limitation applies, the value of this variable is the name of the root domain (a DNS name consisting of a single zero octet).

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetClass.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetClass
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetClass.description: The class of DNS queries that will be sent to the server identified by this row of the table.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetStatus.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetStatus
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetStatus.description: Row status column for this row of the Sbelt table.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetTable.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetTable
rlDnsResCacheRRInetTable.description: This table contains information about all the resource records currently in the resolver's cache.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetEntry.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetEntry
rlDnsResCacheRRInetEntry.description: An entry in the resolvers's cache. Rows may be created only by the resolver. SNMP SET requests may be used to delete rows.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetName.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetName
rlDnsResCacheRRInetName.description: Owner name of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table. As described in RFC-1034, the owner of the record is the domain name were the RR is found.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetClass.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetClass
rlDnsResCacheRRInetClass.description: DNS class of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetType.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetType
rlDnsResCacheRRInetType.description: DNS type of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetTTL.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetTTL
rlDnsResCacheRRInetTTL.description: Time-To-Live of RR in DNS cache. This is the initial TTL value which was received with the RR when it was originally received.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetElapsedTTL.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetElapsedTTL
rlDnsResCacheRRInetElapsedTTL.description: Elapsed seconds since RR was received.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetSourceAddrType.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetSourceAddrType
rlDnsResCacheRRInetSourceAddrType.description: The address type of rlDnsResCacheRRInetSource. Only IPv4, IPv4z, IPv6, and IPv6z addresses are expected, or unknown(0) if datagrams for all local IP addresses are accepted.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetSource.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetSource
rlDnsResCacheRRInetSource.description: Host from which RR was received, 0.0.0.0 if unknown.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetData.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetData
rlDnsResCacheRRInetData.description: RDATA portion of a cached RR. The value is in the format defined for the particular DNS class and type of the resource record.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetStatus.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetStatus
rlDnsResCacheRRInetStatus.description: Status column for the resolver cache table. Since only the agent (DNS resolver) creates rows in this table, the only values that a manager may write to this variable are active(1) and destroy(6).

rlDnsResCacheRRInetIndex.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetIndex
rlDnsResCacheRRInetIndex.description: A value which makes entries in the table unique when the other index values (rlDnsResCacheRRName, rlDnsResCacheRRClass, and rlDnsResCacheRRType) do not provide a unique index.

rlDnsResCacheRRInetPrettyName.name: rlDnsResCacheRRInetPrettyName
rlDnsResCacheRRInetPrettyName.description: Name of the RR at this row in the table. This is identical to the rlDnsResCacheRRName variable, except that character case is preserved in this variable, per DNS conventions.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetTable.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetTable
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetTable.description: The resolver's negative response cache. This table contains information about authoritative errors that have been cached by the resolver.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetEntry.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetEntry
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetEntry.description: An entry in the resolver's negative response cache table. Only the resolver can create rows. SNMP SET requests may be used to delete rows.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQName.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQName
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQName.description: QNAME associated with a cached authoritative error.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQClass.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQClass
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQClass.description: DNS QCLASS associated with a cached authoritative error.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQType.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQType
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetQType.description: DNS QTYPE associated with a cached authoritative error.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetTTL.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetTTL
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetTTL.description: Time-To-Live of a cached authoritative error at the time of the error, it should not be decremented by the number of seconds since it was received. This should be the TTL as copied from the MINIMUM field of the SOA that accompanied the authoritative error, or a smaller value if the resolver implements a ceiling on negative response cache TTLs.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetElapsedTTL.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetElapsedTTL
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetElapsedTTL.description: Elapsed seconds since authoritative error was received.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSourceAddrType.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSourceAddrType
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSourceAddrType.description: The address type of rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSource. Only IPv4, IPv4z, IPv6, and IPv6z addresses are expected, or unknown(0) if datagrams for all local IP addresses are accepted.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSource.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSource
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetSource.description: Host which sent the authoritative error, 0.0.0.0 if unknown.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetCode.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetCode
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetCode.description: The authoritative error that has been cached: nonexistantName(1) indicates an authoritative name error (RCODE = 3). noData(2) indicates an authoritative response with no error (RCODE = 0) and no relevant data. other(3) indicates some other cached authoritative error. At present, no such errors are known to exist. unresolved(4) is used for 'fixed' entries that are currently unresolved.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetStatus.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetStatus
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetStatus.description: Status column for the resolver negative response cache table. Since only the agent (DNS resolver) creates rows in this table, the only values that a manager may write to this variable are active(1) and destroy(6).

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetIndex.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetIndex
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetIndex.description: A value which makes entries in the table unique when the other index values (rlDnsResNCacheErrQName, rlDnsResNCacheErrQClass, and rlDnsResNCacheErrQType) do not provide a unique index.

rlDnsResNCacheErrInetPrettyName.name: rlDnsResNCacheErrInetPrettyName
rlDnsResNCacheErrInetPrettyName.description: QNAME associated with this row in the table. This is identical to the rlDnsResNCacheErrQName variable, except that character case is preserved in this variable, per DNS conventions.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtInetTable.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtInetTable
rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtInetTable.description: Augmenting rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetTable (dns resolver safety belt table) for added info

rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtInetEntry.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtInetEntry
rlDnsResConfigSbeltExtInetEntry.description: A row of the table rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetTable Extended by this definition.

rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetOwner.name: rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetOwner
rlDnsResConfigSbeltInetOwner.description: The DNS server Entry owner. Static if DNS server Entry defined by user, dhcp if received by boot protocol like DHCP.

rlDnsClMinPollingInterval.name: rlDnsClMinPollingInterval
rlDnsClMinPollingInterval.description: The minimum number of seconds that must elapsed between invocations of the resolving procedure for fixed DNS entries which are currently unresolved.
